    image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1515562141207-7a88fb7ce338?w=800&h=500&fit=crop",
    tags: ["avoid scam", "wholesale suppliers", "jewellery", "b2b safety"],
    content: `<h2>Jewellery Wholesale Scams Are More Common Than You Think</h2>
<p>The Indian jewellery wholesale market is largely legitimate and professional — but like any large industry, it attracts bad actors targeting international buyers who cannot easily visit in person. Knowing the warning signs before you engage will protect your business and money.</p>

<h2>Red Flags That Signal a Scam Supplier</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Prices 60–80% below market rate</strong> — If it sounds too good to be true, it is. Legitimate manufacturers have real material and labour costs.</li>
  <li><strong>Vague address</strong> — "India" or a city name with no street address is a major warning sign.</li>
  <li><strong>Refuses video call</strong> — Any genuine manufacturer will show you their workspace on camera.</li>
  <li><strong>Western Union or crypto payment only</strong> — Legitimate exporters accept bank transfer (SWIFT), PayPal, or LC. Untraceable payment demands mean no recourse if things go wrong.</li>
  <li><strong>No business registration details</strong> — Cannot provide GSTIN or IEC means they are not legally registered to export.</li>
  <li><strong>No buyer references</strong> — Established suppliers have a track record. Refusal to share references is a red flag.</li>
  <li><strong>WhatsApp-only communication</strong> — No business email or website suggests an informal, unregistered operation.</li>
  <li><strong>New B2B platform account</strong> — Less than 6 months old with no verified reviews deserves extra scrutiny.</li>
  <li><strong>Pressure tactics</strong> — "Only 3 days left on this price" or "stock running out" are classic manipulation tactics.</li>
  <li><strong>Stock photos from multiple other websites</strong> — Reverse image search product photos. If the same images appear on 10 different supplier sites, the supplier likely has no real inventory.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Protect Your Business</h2>
<p>Verify GSTIN on the GST portal, use escrow or LC payment for first orders, start with small sample orders, and get all terms in a written purchase order. Working with established, referenced suppliers like Gemora Global removes these risks entirely.</p>

<p>Contact Gemora Global on WhatsApp: <a href="https://wa.me/917976341419">+91 7976341419</a></p>`
